---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Ping"
  description="Ping is a P2P social money network. 0.4% flat fee. No FX markup. Open source. Built on the openova.io Sovereign platform."
  path="/about"
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-bg-primary to-bg-secondary py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <h1 class="text-balance text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-text-primary sm:text-6xl">
        Money should move like a message.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        The remittance industry takes 7-15% per transfer and makes recipients wait days.
        For people sending $200 to family back home, that's a week of groceries lost to
        middlemen who add no value.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        Ping cuts the middlemen. USDC moves on Solana in under a second. We charge 0.4%
        to cover the actual cost of off-ramp to GCash / Maya / UPI / M-Pesa / JazzCash.
        No FX markup. Pyth on-chain pricing. The recipient sees the same number their
        sender saw.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary">How we built it</h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        Ping runs on the open-source <a href="https://openova.io" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">openova.io</a>
        Sovereign platform — Kubernetes + Flux GitOps + Cilium service mesh +
        cert-manager + NATS JetStream + CNPG Postgres. We didn't reinvent the
        infrastructure; we used the best-in-class open-source components and
        composed them into a remittance platform.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
        On-chain: USDC on Solana for settlement. Pyth for FX rates.
        Privy MPC for non-custodial wallets. Wise + TransFi for last-mile fiat off-ramp.
        Everything user-facing is auditable on GitHub.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-border-primary bg-bg-secondary py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary">Principles</h2>
      <ul class="mt-8 space-y-6">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="mt-1 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400">✓</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Non-custodial</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-text-secondary">Your USDC is in your Privy MPC wallet. We can't freeze it, can't move it, can't see it without your signature.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="mt-1 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400">✓</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Open source</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-text-secondary">Every line is on GitHub. Reproducible builds. No hidden fees in some closed-source contract.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="mt-1 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400">✓</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">No FX markup</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-text-secondary">Pyth on-chain price. Same rate Bloomberg sees. No spread, no hidden commission.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="mt-1 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400">✓</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">User-first</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-text-secondary">Recipients don't need a wallet, an app download, a seed phrase. Just their phone. Same number their family already calls them on.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
